        <media:content url="https://www.jujubemonster.com/media/posts/104/loneback.png" medium="image" />
            <category term="poetry"/>
            <category term="Chinese poems"/>

        <updated>2026-05-17T13:33:00-07:00</updated>
            <summary type="html">
                <![CDATA[
                        <img src="https://www.jujubemonster.com/media/posts/104/loneback.png" alt="" />
                    蒹葭苍苍，白露为霜。 所谓伊人，在水一方。 The reeds and rushes are deeply green, The white dew has turned to frost. The one of whom I think, Is somewhere by the water’s edge. —《蒹葭》 (Jian Jia)
                ]]>
            </summary>
        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                    <p><img src="https://www.jujubemonster.com/media/posts/104/loneback.png" class="type:primaryImage" alt="" /></p>
                <p class="wp-block-paragraph">蒹葭苍苍，白露为霜。<br>所谓伊人，在水一方。</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The reeds and rushes are deeply green,<br>The white dew has turned to frost.<br>The one of whom I think,<br>Is somewhere by the water’s edge.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">—<strong>《蒹葭》 (Jian Jia)</strong></p>
